  "texts": [
    "Our findings also indicate that there exists a trade-off between safety and utility, so a widely effective defense mechanism may not be the optimal choice for every model.",
    "For example, although \"Tuned Smry.\"",
    "achieves the highest protection levels on PAP for GPT-3.5 (ASR 94% to 4%), it considerably diminishes model helpfulness, with MT-bench scores dropping from 8.97 to 6.65; while \"Adapt Sys.\"",
    "demonstrates effective PAP mitigation in GPT-3.5 and minimally impacts MTbench scores (8.97 to 8.85).",
    "This indicates that \"Adapt Sys.\""
  ]
}